HEADWORD: Aphrasia
<hw>A*phra"si*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>'a</grk> priv. + <grk>fra`sis</grk> speech.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>= <er>Dumbness</er>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>A disorder of speech in which words can be uttered but
not intelligibly joined together.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

